{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"stampable-basaltine-pony","description":"## Why\n\nThe compaction fold claims an all-or-none contract (invariant I1): snapshot written\nfirst, sources renamed to `*.retired`, and on failure every completed rename reversed\nand the snapshot removed. But in `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py` (~lines 235-247) the\nrollback path only *logs* a failed reverse-rename and continues, then unconditionally\nremoves the snapshot and returns failure. Because normal replay excludes `*.retired`\n(`src/rebar/reducer/_cache.py`), a source that failed to restore becomes invisible with\nno snapshot left to carry its folded effect — silent, undetectable data loss that\nviolates the stated contract.\n\n## What\n\n- On any reverse-rename failure during rollback, do **not** delete the snapshot; retain\n  it (or write a recovery sentinel) and emit an explicit\n  `rollback incomplete; run fsck` diagnostic.\n- Ensure `fsck` recognizes and repairs the resulting mixed state (restored active files\n  alongside a retained snapshot).\n- Add fault-injection tests (currently the negative suite injects only at\n  `compact.lock.acquire` and `compact._git`, never in the rename loop).\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py` (rollback branch)\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_cache.py` / fsck repair path (mixed-state recognition)\n- `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_compact_negative.py` (new fault-injection tests)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Forward-rename fault test: inject `OSError` on the 2nd/3rd forward `os.rename`;\n      assert nonzero exit, no active snapshot, every original filename restored, no\n      stray `*.retired`, reduced state deep-equal to pre-compaction, clean `fsck`, and\n      an idempotent re-compaction.\n- [ ] Reverse-rename fault test: inject a forward failure AND a reverse-rename failure;\n      assert the snapshot is NOT deleted, a recoverable diagnostic is emitted, and no\n      source data is lost.\n- [ ] `fsck` deterministically detects and repairs the incomplete-rollback state.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"4001-185c-1a51-44ee","parent_id":"cc4d-7be4-dc0b-497f","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Fix compaction rollback-failure atomicity hazard + rename fault-injection tests"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783886353866964001,"uuid":"9c88c2d0-6bb2-4395-9c00-1ceb3f17c15b"}